  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air then boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cover tightly with <strong>tin foil </strong>and put the dish in the oven for 30 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1660661713635-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1660661713635-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1660661713635-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1660661713635-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1660661713635-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomatoes</strong> into wedges</p><p>Chop your <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and<strong> creamed coconut </strong>in 600ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[780ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1660661716439-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1660661716439-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1660661716439-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1660661716439-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1660661716439-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add <strong>half </strong>the <strong>sliced onion </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to soften</p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>ground turmeric </strong>and <strong>curry powder</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until fragrant</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1660661718464-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1660661718464-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1660661718464-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1660661718464-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1660661718464-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, rinse your <strong>red lentils</strong>, then add them to the pot with the <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a medium-high heat, and cook for 15-20 min or until the lentils are tender and starting to break down</p><p>Once tender, add the<strong> tomato wedges</strong> to the pot and cook for 5 min further or until the tomatoes have softened and the lentils are fully cooked – this is your <strong>tomato & coconut dal</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1660661724476-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1660661724476-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1660661724476-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1660661724476-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1660661724476-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>coconut flakes </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden, then set aside and reserve the pan</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don’t burn!</p><p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>diced chicken thigh</strong>, <strong>garam masala</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to a bowl and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1660661732779-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1660661732779-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1660661732779-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1660661732779-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1660661732779-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>seasoned chicken </strong>and <strong>remaining sliced onion </strong>and cook for 8-10 min or until the chicken is golden and cooked through (no pink meat!)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1660661738865-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1660661738865-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1660661738865-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1660661738865-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1660661738865-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can then chop it finely</p><p>Once the chicken is cooked, add the <strong>chopped spinach </strong>to the pan for 2 min to warm through – this is your <strong>chicken saag</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1660661755729-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1660661755729-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1660661755729-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1660661755729-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1660661755729-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chicken saag </strong>and <strong>tomato & coconut dal </strong>alongside the <strong>basmati rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>toasted coconut flakes</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
